<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: DRIVING-SKILLS CLASSES OFFERED TO SENIORS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Senior citizens who want to sharpen their driving skills and qualify for an 
auto insurance discount can take a class at six South County sites this month. 
</P>
<P>
 Sponsored by the American Assn. of Retired Persons, "55 Alive" is a two-day 
program. 
</P>
<P>
 Once completed, participants will be issued a certificate from the Department 
of Motor Vehicles, which qualifies policy-holders for a senior citizen 
discount. 
</P>
<P>
 Students must be at least 50 years old, although 55 is the minimum age to 
qualify for insurance discounts. The cost for the class is $8. 
</P>
<P>
 Preregistration is required, and those who are interested must call the 
facility where the class is being held to sign up. 
</P>
<P>
 Classes will be held at these locations: 
</P>
<P>
 * Monday and Tuesday, 9:30 a.m. to 2 p.m., San Clemente Senior Center, 242 
Avenida del Mar, (714) 498-3322. 
</P>
<P>
 * Monday and Tuesday, 8 a.m. to noon, Norman P. Murray Center, 24932 Oso 
Viejo, Mission Viejo, (714) 348-2063. 
</P>
<P>
 * Jan. 22 and 29, 9 a.m. to 1 p.m., Laguna Beach Senior Center, 384 Legion St. 
in Lang Park, (714) 497-2441. 
</P>
<P>
 * Jan. 24 and 25, 8:30 a.m. to 12:30 p.m., Laguna Niguel Senior Center, 27261 
La Paz Road, Unit I, (714) 362-2807. 
</P>
<P>
 * Jan. 26 and 27, 1 to 5 p.m., Laguna Hills Senior Center, 24310 Moulton 
Parkway, Unit C, (714) 380-0155. 
</P>
<P>
 * Jan. 28 and 29, 12:30 to 4:30 p.m., Freedom Village Retirement Community, 
23442 El Toro Road, Lake Forest, (714) 472-4700.FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
