<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: PASADENA; SUSPECTS IN 
KILLINGS ARE HIDING HERE, POLICE SAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Pasadena police and the FBI say they believe both suspects still wanted in the 
fatal shootings of three teen-agers on Halloween night are hiding out in 
Pasadena. 
</P>
<P>
 The FBI trailed Herbert McClain, 22, through four states before nearly 
cornering him in Kansas City, Mo., said Charlie J. Parsons, special agent in 
charge of the Los Angeles FBI office. 
</P>
<P>
 Agents believe that McClain returned to Pasadena, his hometown. "He is not a 
mental giant, and people commonly return home," Parsons said at a news 
conference. 
</P>
<P>
 The second suspect, Solomon Bowen, 22, is believed to have remained in hiding 
in Pasadena throughout the investigation, Pasadena Police Chief Jerry Oliver 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 McClain and Bowen are suspects in the ambush-style murders of Steven Coats and 
Reggie Crawford, both 14, and Edgar Evans, 13, as the youths walked home from a 
Halloween party Oct. 31. 
</P>
<P>
 Three other suspects -- Lorenzo Newborn, 23; Aurelius Bailey, 19, and Karl 
Holmes, 19 -- were arrested by Pasadena police Dec. 23. The FBI joined the 
investigation Dec. 27, Oliver said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
