<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: BUENA PARK; COUNCIL OKS $258,000 FOR ALLEYWAY REPAIRS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DEBRA CANO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Alleys off Beach Boulevard between Manchester Boulevard and Franklin Street 
are in such bad shape that the City Council this week approved spending 
$258,000 to repair the narrow drives behind businesses. 
</P>
<P>
 The council awarded the construction contract to Nobest Inc. of Garden 
Grove.To pay for the alleyway rehabilitation, the city will use federal grant 
money. 
</P>
<P>
 The project, approved by the council last November, will involve paving the 
deteriorated public alleys and installing gutters to improve drainage. The 
ramps and driveway accesses on both sides of Beach Boulevard will also be 
paved. 
</P>
<P>
 On the east side of the boulevard, improvements will be made from Manchester 
Boulevard to Franklin Street and, on the west side, from just north of 5th 
Street to Franklin Street. 
</P>
<P>
 Construction will be done in segments to minimize any inconvenience so that 
customers and employees will still have access to businesses and homes, said 
Nabil S. Henein, deputy city engineer. 
</P>
<P>
 Improvements are expected to start Jan. 24. Notifications of the construction 
schedule will also be sent next week to business owners and residents, Henein 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 The project is expected to be completed by the end of March, weather 
permitting.DEBRA CANO 
</P>
</TEXT>
