<TEXT>
<P>
 * I want to respond to Joseph Ball's letter (Dec. 17) regarding the findings 
of the Warren Commission and his statement that "After 30 years no one doubts 
that Oswald killed Kennedy and wounded Connally." 
</P>
<P>
 I hate to burst his bubble, but I've had doubts for years. While I don't know 
who killed President Kennedy, I have every right to reject the Warren 
Commission's lone assassin theory and will continue to have doubts about it so 
long as evidence surrounding the case continues to be suppressed. 
</P>
<P>
 BRIAN HAYES 
