<HEADLINE>
<P>
2 MEN ARRESTED IN THEFT, EVADING POLICE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAVID REYES, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two men who snatched clothing from a Mervyn's Department Store and then led 
police on a high-speed chase on the San Diego Freeway during rush hour were 
arrested after they rear-ended another car, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The chase began about 5:30 p.m. at the Mervyn's at 7777 Edinger Ave., after 
two men grabbed men's clothes, ran to a pickup and got on the freeway at Beach 
Boulevard, said Huntington Beach Police Sgt. Larry Miller. 
</P>
<P>
 The pair headed south, got off the freeway at Brookhurst Street in Fountain 
Valley but made a U-turn and returned to the freeway going north. 
</P>
<P>
 Miller said the truck got off the freeway at Magnolia Street and struck a car 
at Foxglove Avenue. The driver and passenger then surrendered. 
</P>
<P>
 Daniel Eric Vasquez, 24, of Westminster, and Richard Ray Sandoval, 24, of Lake 
Elsinore were arrested on suspicion of burglary, evading police and drug 
possession, Miller said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police found $500 in men's clothing and 3 1/2 grams of methamphetamine powder 
packaged in bindles, Miller said. 
</P>
<P>
 The men were taken to the Huntington Beach Jail, where they were held on 
$10,000 bail each. 
</P>
