<HEADLINE>
<P>
SCHOOL BOARD VOTE A BARRIER TO REFORM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Shame on Burbank School Board members Joseph Hooven and Elena Hubbell for 
voting against the John Muir Middle School request for staff development time. 
</P>
<P>
 Don't they read anything about education reform? Reform can't happen without 
teachers' having time to talk to other teachers. 
</P>
<P>
 The California Department of Education's plan, "Second to None," calls for 
schools to provide planning time for teachers. Muir's students would have 
benefited from the creative teaching methods their teachers could have 
developed during those two hours. 
</P>
<P>
 You can't shout school reform and expect it to happen by magic. Effective 
change takes time and planning. Everyone loses when school boards care more 
about the vote than about education. 
</P>
<P>
 ADRIENNE MACK 
</P>
<P>
 Shadow Hills 
</P>
<P>
 Mack is a Los Angeles high school English teacher.  
