<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VALLEY FOCUS: LAKE VIEW TERRACE; PANEL WILL DISCUSS SECURITY AT NEW LAKE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEPHANIE STASSEL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A panel of government officials will be available to answer questions about 
maintenance and security for the proposed 15-acre lake in the Hansen Dam 
Recreation Area at a community meeting Monday evening sponsored by the Lake 
View Terrace Improvement Assn. 
</P>
<P>
 Officials from the city Recreation and Parks Department and the Army Corps of 
Engineers are expected to attend, in addition to Los Angeles City Councilman 
Richard Alarcon and representatives of Los Angeles City Councilman Joel Wachs, 
Assemblyman Richard Katz (D-Sylmar) and Congressman Howard Berman (D-Panorama 
City). 
</P>
<P>
 Groundbreaking for the new lake in the west end of the recreation area is 
expected in June, said Rose Castaneda, administrative assistant for Berman. The 
federal government has approved more than $5 million to improve the Hansen Dam 
property, which is owned by the Army Corps of Engineers. 
</P>
<P>
 "We want something really nice and we want them to tell us how they will do 
it," said Eileen Barry, board member of the Lake View Terrace Improvement Assn. 
</P>
<P>
 The community meeting is scheduled for 7:30 p.m. at the Lake View Terrace 
Recreation Center at 11075 Foothill Blvd., Lake View Terrace. STEPHANIE STASSEL 
</P>
</TEXT>
