<TEXT>
<P>
 A top state official has reappointed Oxnard School District trustee Mary 
Barreto to a council that advises state Department of Education officials on 
policy issues dealing with ethnicity. 
</P>
<P>
 Barreto was appointed this week by acting state Supt. of Public Instruction 
William Dawson to serve a third consecutive year on the 14-member Advisory 
Council on Hispanic Affairs.She is the only representative from Ventura County. 
</P>
<P>
 The council meets three times a year to discuss a range of issues that in the 
past have included the state's policies on bilingual education, the voucher 
proposal and the criteria for the hiring of teachers, a state official said. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's a wonderful experience," Barreto said of her time on the board. "I 
really feel the board makes a difference." 
</P>
<P>
 This year, Barreto said the board will play a role in the selection of a new 
state superintendent. 
</P>
