<P>
WEST VALLEY FOCUS: NORTHRIDGE; ROBBER SOUGHT AFTER STORE CLERK IS SHOT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TIMOTHY WILLIAMS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police continued to search for a man who shot and wounded a clerk during a 
robbery at a Northridge record store, detectives said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 The clerk, Jony Parker, is in serious condition at Northridge Hospital Medical 
Center with a bullet wound to the upper torso, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Detectives are looking for the gunman and a second man who witnesses told 
police drove the suspect away from the Music Plus record store at 8876 Corbin 
Ave. after the attack Thursday morning. 
</P>
<P>
 Police have described the suspects as males in their early to mid-20s. 
</P>
<P>
 The incident occurred about 11:45 a.m. when a man walked into the store, 
brandished a pistol and told Parker to give him money, said Los Angeles Police 
Detective Mike Brandt. 
</P>
<P>
 Parker handed over money from a cash register, but the man shot him anyway, 
Brandt said. 
</P>
<P>
 After the attack, the gunman got into a small white car outside the store and 
was driven away by the second man, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Investigators are not sure why the robber shot Parker or how much money he 
escaped with. 
</P>
<P>
 There were several people inside the store at the time, but many customers 
were unaware there had been a robbery until after the gunman fled, Brandt said. 
TIMOTHY WILLIAMS 
</P>
