WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: CARPINTERIA; VICTIM OF COAST CAR ACCIDENT IDENTIFIED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A man who died in a car that skidded off the Pacific Coast Highway into the 
ocean has been identified as Thomas Gamble, 30, of Carpinteria, coroner's 
officials said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 The accident occurred as Gamble and Orlander Drake, 24, of Isla Vista were 
driving north on U.S. 1 near Sycamore Cove at about 8 p.m. Thursday.Drake 
attempted to pass another car, lost control and hit a dirt embankment on the 
right side. He then spun back across the road toward the ocean, California 
Highway Patrol officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 After crossing a gravel shoulder, Drake's car plunged down the embankment and 
landed upside-down in the ocean. 
</P>
<P>
 Gamble, who was sitting in the front passenger's seat, drowned, said Deputy 
Coroner Zelmira Isaac. Drake swam from the car and survived. He was treated at 
St. John's Regional Medical Center for minor injuries and released, CHP 
officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 No citations have been issued, authorities said. JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
