<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTH COAST LEAGUE BOYS' BASKETBALL; JUNIOR VARSITY COACHES FIGHT AFTER GAME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRIS FOSTER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A fight broke out between coaches after a junior varsity basketball game 
between Mater Dei and Dana Hills Friday night at UC Irvine's Bren Center. 
</P>
<P>
 Junior varsity assistants Jason Quinn of Mater Dei and Dennis Dickens of Dana 
Hills had to be separated by campus police after Quinn appeared to punch 
Dickens.Dana Hills varsity players, who were warming up at the time, charged 
the bench and had to be restrained, as did several fans who attempted to come 
out of the stands. 
</P>
<P>
 The incident occurred after Mater Dei's 75-47 victory. Witnesses said Dana 
Hills coaches complained to Mater Dei coaches that the Monarchs had run up the 
score, and an argument ensued. It grew more intense, and Quinn charged Dickens, 
throwing a punch before the two fell to the ground. 
</P>
<P>
 A Mater Dei official claimed Dickens made a derogatory remark before the 
fight. 
</P>
<P>
 There were no arrests, and officials from both schools met after the game to 
investigate the matter. CHRIS FOSTER 
</P>
