<TEXT>
<P>
 Braden Weber had 18 points and 14 rebounds and Chris Ott added 15 points to 
power host St. Francis High to a 58-52 victory over Bishop Amat on Friday night 
in a Del Rey League boys' basketball game. 
</P>
<P>
 Trailing, 27-19, at halftime, St. Francis took a 39-38 lead at the end of the 
third quarter and never trailed again. The win was the eighth in a row for the 
Golden Knights (12-4, 3-0 in league) and their 11th victory in 12 games. 
</P>
<P>
 In other boys' basketball games: 
</P>
<P>
 Glendale 58, Crescenta Valley 48 -- Ramon Jose scored 14 of his 21 points in 
the second half to lead the Dynamiters (13-4) in a Pacific League opener at 
Glendale. Jose, who made nine of 17 shots, was six for eight in the second 
half. 
</P>
