<HEADLINE>
<P>
FATHER JOHN ZANETOS; EX-PASADENA CLERIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Father John Zanetos, the retired priest of St. Anthony's Greek Orthodox Church 
of Pasadena, has died. He was 73. 
</P>
<P>
 Zanetos, who headed the Pasadena church from 1982 until his retirement in 
1986, died Jan. 1 in Boca Raton, Fla.He had suffered a heart attack and stroke 
Nov. 19. 
</P>
<P>
 A native of Cyprus, Zanetos came to the United States in 1937 and became a 
citizen. He was educated at the Greek Orthodox Seminary in Pomfret, Conn., and 
the Hartford Seminary. 
</P>
<P>
 In 1956, after serving in various churches in New York, he was named dean of 
the Greek Orthodox Cathedral of New England in Boston, where he remained for 26 
years. 
</P>
<P>
 After he retired in Florida, Zanetos organized the Retired Greek Orthodox 
Clergy of America and was its president for four years. 
</P>
<P>
 Zanetos is survived by his wife, Irene; his father, Costas, of Cyprus; a son, 
Dean, of Los Angeles; a daughter, Eugenia Buba, of Andover, Mass., and four 
grandchildren. 
</P>
<P>
 The family has asked that any memorial donations be made to the Hellenic 
College, 50 Goddard Ave., Brookline, Mass. 02146. 
</P>
</TEXT>
