<P>
THOUSANDS FLEE AUSTRALIAN FIRES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Tree-lined streets exploded into infernos today while thousands of people 
jammed into cars with their belongings and fled huge brush fires raging in the 
suburbs of Sydney, Australia's biggest city. 
</P>
<P>
 Thousands of houses were feared to be in jeopardy. 
</P>
<P>
 More than 130 fires were blazing today along the 750-mile eastern seaboard of 
New South Wales state. Witnesses reported seeing flames 80 feet high and walls 
of fire miles long racing through bush land. Police said they suspect that 
arsonists set more than half the fires. 
</P>
<P>
 Earlier in the week, three people were killed in the fires. 
