<TEXT>
<P>
 Money Supply Dips: The Federal Reserve said the measure of the nation's basic 
money supply known as M2 fell in the week ended Dec. 27 to a seasonally 
adjusted $3,549.8 billion, down $6.9 billion from a revised $3,556.7 billion 
the week before.An even broader measure, M3, fell $6.7 billion to $4,209.0 
billion from $4,216.6 billion. The narrowest measure, M1, rose $1.1 billion to 
$1,134.3 billion from $1,133.2 billion. M1 includes cash in circulation, 
checking deposits and non-bank traveler's checks. M2 is M1 plus accounts such 
as savings deposits and money market mutual funds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
