<TEXT>
<P>
 Diceon Layoffs: Diceon Electronics Inc., a maker of computer circuit boards, 
said Friday it will lay off about 160 employees, 80 of whom work at the 
company's Irvine headquarters. All operations and administrative departments 
will be affected by the 14% reduction in Diceon's 1,130-person work force, 
Chief Executive Officer Peter Jonas said.The layoffs will result in a one-time 
charge of about $600,000 for the three months ended Dec. 31. That quarter's 
results will be announced at the end of January, the company said. "We hope 
this action will turn things around and get us back to profitability," Jonas 
said. For its 1993 fiscal year, which ended Sept. 30, Diceon reported a loss of 
$16.3 million, or $3.18 a share, on sales of $99.2 million. And in December, 
the company was de-listed from the Nasdaq market because of insufficient 
capital. Its stock now trades at about 25 cents a share over the counter. The 
other employees to be laid off by the company work at offices in Mountain View 
in Northern California and in Nashua, N.H. 
</P>
</TEXT>
