<HEADLINE>
<P>
TV BLACKOUT LOOMS FOR SUNDAY'S GAME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Raiders' playoff game against the Broncos on Sunday was a little less than 
7,000 tickets shy of a sellout late Friday, according to Raider executive 
assistant Al LoCasale. 
</P>
<P>
 The NFL had granted the Raiders a two-day extension to sell out the 
67,800-seat Coliseum, but if the stadium is not sold out by 1 p.m. today, the 
game will be blacked out in Los Angeles. 
</P>
</TEXT>
