<HEADLINE>
<P>
BUCKEYE COACH BREAKS ANKLE IN FALL ON ICE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ohio State basketball Coach Randy Ayers broke his right ankle on Friday when 
he fell on ice outside St. John Arena. 
</P>
<P>
 Ayers underwent surgery Friday night at Ohio State Medical Center. Christopher 
Kaeding, an orthopedic surgeon, inserted a plate and several screws into Ayers' 
ankle. The coach will remain in the hospital a day or two, Kaeding added. 
</P>
<P>
 Ayers fell as the team was boarding a bus for the airport and a flight to 
Madison, Wis., for today's game against Wisconsin. 
</P>
<P>
 Assistant Dave Cecutti will coach the team in Ayers' absence. 
</P>
<P>
 Ayers should be able to accompany the team to Ann Arbor, Mich., for Thursday's 
game against Michigan, Kaeding said. 
</P>
