<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE LEAGUE BOYS' BASKETBALL; SAVANNA'S RALLY STOPS WESTERN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PETER BARZILAI, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 It wasn't pretty, but the Savanna boys' basketball team will take Friday 
night's 50-46 victory over host Western in an Orange League opener. 
</P>
<P>
 Savanna (7-7, 1-0 in league) trailed for most of the game before taking the 
lead with a little over four minutes left, when Dan Avila converted a 
three-point play with a free throw, giving the Rebels a 42-41 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 "Western makes you look bad," Savanna Coach C.D. Snider said. "They run their 
offense so well, that if it wasn't for Dan Avila, I don't know what would have 
happened." 
</P>
<P>
 Avila scored seven points in the fourth quarter, and finished with 10 points 
and eight rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
 Western (8-6, 0-1), which beat Savanna last Thursday, 57-46, took a 26-22 lead 
at halftime, and increased the lead to 35-25 with a 9-3 run to open the third 
quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 However, the Rebels countered with a 10-2 run, cutting Western's lead to 37-35 
entering the fourth quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 "We wanted to run the ball and they didn't," Snider said. "They were able to 
get some runs and so were we, but they just played their offense so well." 
</P>
<P>
 Western held the ball for nearly two minutes to open the fourth quarter before 
Paul Lindemeyer hit a jump shot. Lindemeyer finished with 11 points and eight 
rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
 The difference down the stretch, though, was Savanna's free-throw shooting, as 
the Rebels converted on all seven attempts. 
</P>
<P>
 "We are very proud of that," Snider said. "That is where you win big games and 
championships." 
</P>
<P>
 Todd Wilson led Savanna in scoring with 14 points; the Pioneers were led by 
Neil Hensley's game-high 18 points, along with Brandon Brennan's 11. 
</P>
<P>
 "This is a huge victory for us," Snider said. "It gives us a great start to 
the league season, and we're usually not comfortable playing here." 
</P>
<P>
 In other league games: 
</P>
<P>
 Magnolia 67, Anaheim 55 -- Brandon Harvey scored 24 points and Frank Henderson 
21 for Magnolia (1-0 in league) in its league opener. 
</P>
<P>
 Valencia 53, Brea-Olinda 48 -- Valencia (7-8, 1-0) won its league opener 
behind Erik Jackley's 12-point effort. 
</P>
</TEXT>
