<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP NOTES: PACIFICA MOVES KENNEDY GAME TO AVOID BINGO NIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAVE McKIBBEN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Because of the following the Pacifica boys' basketball has suddenly developed, 
its Garden Grove League game next week against Kennedy is being moved from 
Wednesday to Thursday night. Wednesday also happens to be bingo night at 
Pacifica. 
</P>
<P>
 Pacifica Coach Bob Becker said the school could not handle the bingo and 
basketball crowds on campus the same night.Bingo fans have always been rather 
intense at Pacifica, but until this season the basketball fans were largely 
apathetic. However, Pacifica is 10-1 this season and ranked sixth in Orange 
County. 
</P>
<P>
 "Our fast-paced style of play is rather infectious," Becker said. "We've got 
people keep coming back for more after they see us play." 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 The Costa Mesa-Estancia girls basketball showdown took on added significance 
Thursday night when it was announced before the game that a spare rib dinner at 
a local restaurant would be awarded to this year's series winner. 
</P>
<P>
 Costa Mesa won the first meeting, 52-51, in overtime. Estancia can still win 
the rib dinner if it defeats Costa Mesa by more than a point in the final 
meeting. Also on the line is the prestigious Lady Bell Trophy, which was rung 
by players on both teams before Thursday's game. DAVE McKIBBEN 
</P>
</TEXT>
